        public java.lang.String getPortGroup()
        The name of this port's group. A port group is a mapping that is configured on a storage system between a collection of ports, a collection of volumes and a collection of hosts that use those volumes. This name is what the storage system uses to identify the port group. mapped known by Vipr to this port
